# Cursor Project Rules: TCC Modeler (CF Model App)

## Project purpose

This app is a **TCC/CF Modeler** for physician compensation. It lets compensation administrators:

- Upload provider and market survey data (CSV or XLSX) with optional column mapping.
- Run single-provider scenarios (provider → scenario → market → results) and batch scenarios across all providers.
- Use the CF Optimizer and Productivity Target tools for specialty-level modeling.
- View reports (saved runs, TCC/wRVU percentiles, impact, quick-run CF, custom CF by specialty, market positioning).
- Export results to XLSX/CSV.

Data and scenarios live in browser memory and `localStorage`; there is no backend.

---

## Tech stack and tools

- **React 18+** with **TypeScript** and **Vite**
- **Tailwind CSS** and **shadcn/ui** (Radix primitives)
- **Recharts** for charts
- **PapaParse** (CSV) and **SheetJS (xlsx)** for file parsing and export
- **Vitest** for unit tests
- State: React state + custom hooks (`use-app-state`, `use-provider-actions`, etc.); no Redux
- Persistence: `localStorage` via `lib/storage.ts`, `lib/batch-storage.ts`, `lib/optimizer-storage.ts`, `lib/productivity-target-storage.ts`
- Web Workers for batch and optimizer runs (`workers/batch-worker.ts`, `workers/optimizer-worker.ts`)

---

## Folder structure

- `src/components/` — Shared UI (layout, upload/mapping, batch flows, charts, `ui/` for shadcn)
- `src/features/` — Feature modules: `data/`, `optimizer/`, `productivity-target/`, `reports/`, `help/`
- `src/hooks/` — App state and actions (`use-app-state`, `use-provider-actions`, `use-batch-actions`, etc.)
- `src/lib/` — Core logic: compute, parse, storage, engines, export (XLSX/CSV)
- `src/types/` — TypeScript types (provider, market, scenario, batch, optimizer, upload)
- `src/utils/` — Helpers (format, math, aggregate-fte, sample-upload)
- `src/workers/` — Web Workers for batch and optimizer

Do not put feature-specific code in `src/` root; keep it under `src/features/<feature>/`.

---

## Data and column mapping

- **Provider file:** one row per provider; expected columns (e.g. `providerId`, `providerName`, `specialty`, `baseSalary`, `totalWRVUs`, `workRVUs`, FTE fields, etc.) are defined in `types/provider.ts`. Headers can be mapped on upload via `ColumnMapping` in `types/upload.ts`.
- **Market file:** one row per specialty (or specialty + type/region) with percentile columns (`TCC_25`–`TCC_90`, `WRVU_25`–`WRVU_90`, `CF_25`–`CF_90`). See `types/market.ts` and `lib/parse-file.ts`.
- Mapping and parsing: `lib/parse-file.ts` — `buildDefaultProviderMapping` / `buildDefaultMarketMapping`, `applyProviderMapping` / `applyMarketMapping`. Validation errors are returned as `errors: string[]` and shown in the upload UI.

---

## Export and outputs

- Exports are **XLSX and CSV** only (no DOCX/PDF). See `lib/single-scenario-export.ts`, `lib/batch-export.ts`, and other `*-export.ts` in `lib/`.
- Batch results and scenario results are exported as wide rows (provider × scenario) with match status, risk, percentiles, governance flags (e.g. `fmvCheckSuggested`).

---

## Governance and FMV

- FMV risk is computed from TCC percentiles (e.g. `lib/optimizer-constants.ts`: `FMV_RED_FLAG_PERCENTILE`, `getFmvRiskLevel`).
- UI surfaces “FMV check suggested” and risk levels via `components/governance-flags.tsx` and optimizer/report tables.
- Optional: an audit log for FMV-related overrides or high-percentile approvals can be added in `lib/audit.ts` (non-PII only).

---

## Code practices

- Use the existing hooks for state and persistence; do not introduce Redux unless the product roadmap requires it.
- Keep compute and engine logic in `lib/` (e.g. `compute.ts`, `optimizer-engine.ts`, `productivity-target-engine.ts`); keep UI in `components/` and `features/`.
- Use TypeScript types from `src/types/` for provider, market, scenario, batch, optimizer, and upload shapes.
- For new forms or validation, consider zod (or similar) for persisted state and DTOs; validate on load from `localStorage` to avoid crashes on corrupted data.
- Use the shared `LoadingState` component and existing progress patterns for async operations; use Error Boundaries for render-time errors.

---

## File naming

- **camelCase** for variables and functions
- **PascalCase** for components
- **kebab-case** for filenames (e.g. `upload-and-mapping.tsx`, `optimizer-configure-stage.tsx`)
- Use `.tsx` only for files that contain JSX; use `.ts` for pure logic

---

## Testing

- Unit tests (Vitest) live next to the code (e.g. `lib/compute.test.ts`, `lib/optimizer-engine.test.ts`, `lib/productivity-target-engine.test.ts`). Add tests for new engines and for `parse-file` / mapping when changing validation or column handling.
